			<br>
			
				<img src="/i/p.gif" height=8 width=150 border=0 alt=""><br>
				
			<a href='/eq/view_profile?user.id=1772'>







</a><br>
			


			
			<p>
			






<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=PVP&message.id=91#M91">1</a> of 94
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 1189 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<i>Bah, Brenlo closed the thread just as I was typing this up.  And here I thought we were being relatively civil, for Zekkers.....<br><br>If Devs are still looking to us for suggestions, etc., let's do them here. This was going to be my contribution to the thread before it closed:</i><br><br>Wouldn't think they're going to do anything drastic like hard-code the teams on Tallon and Vallon, or merge Neuts and Goods into one team on Sullon. (For one thing, you'd have to boot the Neut DEs to the Evil team.  For another, there's way too much bad blood between Neuts and Goods, I think.) <br><br>What are we left with? Balancing classes, not teams. And doing something about various forms of training on Sullon - RezBox and Bard DA, especially. Since it is the official "No Rules" server, I doubt that other forms of training will be specifically disallowed. Some solutions for training have already been proposed. <br><br>So, what about classes? On this thread, folks think that overpowered classes include SKs, and to a lesser extent Necros and Wizards. Bards, too, but more because they're hard to kill, not because they do a lot of killing themselves.  Shamans underpowered? I dunno about that. Un-nerfing Ranger bows (not all the way, just a bit) would help out the Goods and Neuts a bit. <br><br>I still think that Zone Control on Sullon should mean something, but it's hard to see what that could be.  Hm... PoK portals - what about putting two in each zone, and making each one one-way?  So, you could zone into, say, Butcherblock, but to zone back out to PoK, you'd have to go to another book. Sure, you'd still have exit-book camping, but it would make "book dancing" a bit harder. <br><br>Or, how about if zone control in zones with books meant that only characters from that team could use the book? And then, do away with non-PvP zones? Goods would fight to make GFay safe, in that case.  Think about it - you'd have to devote some effort to protecting your home zones so that you could have some place to train, get supplies, etc. Would make zones worth fighting for, in that case.  <br><br>Sorry, my imagination is going wild. <br><br>Oh, and fixes to the points board, and some kind of rewards for Insiginias, on Sullon, would be cool. Maybe something like turning them in for Tribute-type points. And, whatever happened to the "Missionaries" - I think that's what they were called - they NPCs in starting towns that sold the special, Sullon-only Bracer of {your deity}? Was nice to be able to get something on Sullon that you couldn't get on other servers, gave you sort of a feeling of being a bit out of the ordinary. <br><br>Just some random thoughts. Thanks in  general, Devs, for looking at life on the Zeks.<p>Message Edited by Kharlisht on <span class=date_text>04-09-2004</span> <span class=time_text>04:38 PM</span>	
		</td></tr>
		<tr>
		
		<td class="msg_date_cell" valign=bottom nowrap>
		<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
		 <span class=date_text>04-09-2004</span> <span class=time_text>04:38 PM</span>
		</span>
		</td>

		
