		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>[quote]</DIV>
<DIV>2)&nbsp; Training</DIV>
<DIV>It's not the concept of training that bothers me - this IS a no rules server, and </DIV>
<DIV>training should be an option.&nbsp; What is ridiculous is the ease of training.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>Anyone with a TL/rez box setup can win a 1 vs. 72 "fight" every time.&nbsp; I'd </DIV>
<DIV>suggest that: <BR>a) if you move, you automatically decline a rez or TL<BR>b) all instant gate effects get a cast time - I'd suggest 1 second<BR>c) all mobs that summon begin to summon on aggro, not on damage</DIV>
<DIV>[/quote]</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Xefin posted these thoughts in his Fixing Sullon Zek thread.&nbsp; I really liked 2a), I thought 2b) was already in the game, but 2c) may break legitimate PvE pulling tactics.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I would instead add the twist that if you are FD, then you become full item-lootable.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I still maintain that full item-loot and a severe death penalty is the direction to go in.&nbsp; The FVie server&nbsp;has some additional play mechanics that are worth evaluating in a PvP setting (role-playing would not be one of them.)</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>-chucklevz</DIV>
<DIV>"The goal of PvP in Everquest is to manage and control access to PvE content."</DIV>	
