		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>Item loot in EQ benefits those who have all no-drop items, because they have nothing to lose.&nbsp; The way EQ is now (with all the no-drop items), I dont think it would help much, it would probably discourage new players to a server, because generally, newer players are in bazaar purchased equipment, until they can get the no-drop stuff.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Ive been on SZ too long I guess.&nbsp; Ive grown to dislike the griefing aspect of PvP.&nbsp; Thing like corpse camping, training, etc, dont encourage more players to play PvP, they frustrate potential PvP'ers and make tons of people quit.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Face it, for EQ to pay attention to PvP, they need to make PvP more attractive to players, not less.&nbsp; Why?&nbsp; Because its all about $$.&nbsp; IF you get a higher population on PvP servers, EQ will think its more profitable to pay attention to PvP.&nbsp; IF you force players away from PvP servers, EQ will think PvP is a waste of money and resources, and wont pay any attention to it.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Now dont get me wrong.&nbsp; I dont think PvP should be easy, I just think it should be fun.&nbsp; There should be some game mechanics that dont allow (or at least discourages) the griefing that goes on currently.&nbsp; People quitting PvP servers due to griefing does not help the cause of EQ putting resources into improving, or adding content for PvP.&nbsp; </DIV>	
		</td></tr>
