		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<P>Other thread Locked just before I posted also <img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-indifferent.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0> Here are my thoughts on good changes.</P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<DIV><FONT size=2>
<P>The "Top" 3 PvP classes have manaburn/instagate/strongroot, Deathtouch (AA HT), and lifeburn. Even without these abilities they remain the top 3 PvP classes in my opinion. GREATLY scaling down these abilities in pvp would be a good move to somewhat balace the warfare.</P>
<P>Pure melee classes are&nbsp;very weak in pvp unless they are elemental/time geared+. I liked the idea of increasing their Hit Box radius if that is possible.</P>
<P>TRAINING: Make it illegal and bannable. Rez-box, Horse, ghosting/plugging, instagate and bards . .. no comment needed. One player can single handedly end virtually ANY PVE raid anywhere anytime. Training is not Player Versus Player and it has no place in Everquest.</P>
<P>PvP Immune zones: Having a player "book" out to a pvp immune zone, healing himself with thier cleric bot, and zoning back in over and over isn't exactly fair and balanced PvP in my eyes. Luclin Nexus Portals went off in certain time intervals making them a mode of travel but NOT an instant escape. My idea lies somewhere in the middle. Put a "Wait Period" on PoP books. For example when you click on one you would have to wait near it for say thirty seconds or one minute to be able to zone to POKnowledge or POTranquility.</P></FONT></DIV>
<DIV></DIV>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							_______________<br>Kainzzo_Smells<br>The *Gnome* Lord<br>Sullon Zek!
