	<tr>
	
		<td class="msg_user_cell" width="150" valign=top>
		
			 









<a href='/eq/view_profile?user.id=1353'  class="auth_text"  style="font-weight:bold;" >	
<span style='color:#CC6600;font-weight:bold; '>Kawaru</span></a>
			<br>
			
			<span style="font-size: 8pt;">
			Master<br>
			
				Posts: 179<br>
				
				Registered: 03-01-2004
				
			</span>
			


			
			<br>
			
				<img src="/i/p.gif" height=8 width=150 border=0 alt=""><br>
				
			<a href='/eq/view_profile?user.id=1353'>







<img src="/eq/i/icons/Classes/magician.gif" border=0 alt=""/></a><br>
			


			
			<p>
			






<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=PVP&message.id=151#M151">13</a> of 94
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 978 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			There are some things that I can see them doing, and a whole bunch of things I don't.  One, I doubt that they will make any drastic changes to the basic rulesets on any of the PvP servers.  I.e., not hard-coding VT/TZ (as much as I'd love to see it happen) or combining the Good and Neutral teams on Sullon, or allowing looting of No Drop items on Rallos Zek.  Nor would I expect massive gameplay changes such as bards not being able to sing while moving.  Things that move them too far from the blue server codebase are unlikely to happen.  Nor are they likely to make concessions to teams/guilds that are "behind" in PvE and thus behind in PvP.  I wouldn't expect people to wake up one morning with keys to VT and flags to PoT.  Does it suck to have less gear than others?  Yes, it does, it really, really does.  When tanks in most x-team guilds have more hit points unbuffed than my guild's MT does in raid buffs you know there is a discrepancy.  But you learn to live with it.<br><br>What I can see happening are relatively minor changes and fixes that can have a large impact.  Things like revamping the resistance system, for instance, or making horses follow the normal buff rules.  These are things that would alter PvP but have a fairly negligable impact on PvE.  In that vein my best hopes would be the following:<br><br>1) Change the resist system to make people with VT/Elemental level resists still somewhat vulnerable to spells.  This doesn't mean that I should be able to land Root each time, every time on someone with a 400+ MR, but I should be able to land something other than Mala every once in a while.  As it stands now I rarely bother because the time spent casting offensive spells can be better utilized on something that might help someone who *can* do damage.<br><br>2) Fix casting level limits in PvP.  If a spell can't affect NPCs past a certain level it shouldn't bloody well effect PCs above that level either.  <br><br>3) Allow pets to take on their casters' resists in PvP.  As it stands now if you look at them funny it sticks.  Beastlord pets are in a little better shape here as their innate MR is pretty high, but mage pets are pretty pathetic.<br><br>4) Something has to be done about horses.  Heck, in my opinion something has to be done about Selo's as well, but I don't think that will happen.  But back to horses ....  That they overwrite snare is a bug, it is the only movement enhancer that does.  <br><br>5) Fix the issue with people getting healed when they zone.  I know why it's in the game, I was around when people would mysteriously die when they zoned at low hit points.  Has to be a better solution, though.<br><br>6) Fix the water plane.  In places where there is water it can get a little crazy.  Especially since melee doesn't have the same restrictions.  <br><br>7) Fix ghosting.  I can't tell you how many times I've lost people in hilly terrain then found them only to discover they weren't actually there.  <br><br>8) Personally I'm alright with Manaburn, Lifeburn, and Harm Touch.  In part because they server to counteract some of the craziness of bards and high-speed horses.  But I recognize that they are a little ... uneven in application, especially with SKs with a lot of AAs.  Maybe add in a resistance check only in PvP, if that is possible.<br><br>I've seen a lot of people saying "it's not fair that ..." when talking about PvP.  The problem is there is no way to make PvP "fair."  People with more gear will always have the advantage.  People who come upon their opponents wounded or low on mana will always have the advantage.  People with numbers will (generally) have the advantage.  These situations are all "unfair."  If you're on a PvP server you aren't dueling.  You aren't ready and waiting for each and every encounter that happens (unless you're as paranoid as I am and compulsively hit /who every 30 seconds <img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-happy.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0>).  But what they can do is hopefully make things a little more balanced.  Currently PvP is suffering by being left to languish with PvE balancing.  The biggest example of that is in gear, but there are others.  I'm hoping that some of that can be corrected in the next few months.
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							Menre Nar'tredok<br>Arch Mage of the Crimson Praetorian<br>Blood and Honor!
							</div>
								
