		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>Bards are an awesome pvp class, but above all else they are balanced. I hear alot of complaining that you're unable to kill a bard, but <STRONG>how often are bards getting killshots on you?</STRONG></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Thus the tradeoff: we're&nbsp;difficult to kill and we can dispell/drain very effectively, <STRONG>however it comes at the expense of having the second lowest pvp&nbsp;damage output of any class. </STRONG>(Since we have no damage songs with a usable resist modifier, our melee is the only form of damage, which is second worst of all capable classes). I cannot cut through a wizard chain rune-ing, and thats assuming they are stationary.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Am I saying wizards are misbalanced? Absolutely not. The best offensive capabilities with no utility. <STRONG>Tradeoffs, tradeoffs, tradeoffs</STRONG>. Every class is good at something, but can't do everything.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Take manadrain if you like, in the POP era of pvp <STRONG>a safezone is 5 steps away at all times</STRONG>. No caster sits around oom waiting to die by my fury of papercuts. I know that if I actually want to fight somebody I can't even use manadrain or they'll run.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>That being said, I think its really good that people brought up safe zones. Taking those away, save for the bazaar, would be an incredible step in the right direction. I think we could consider this a huge success if the next patch weakened harmtouch and removed safezones.</DIV>	
