			<br><blockquote><hr>Astrall-TZ wrote:<br><DIV>Bards are an awesome pvp class, but above all else they are balanced. I hear alot of complaining that you're unable to kill a bard, but <STRONG>how often are bards getting killshots on you?</strong></div><DIV> </div><DIV>Thus the tradeoff: we're difficult to kill and we can dispell/drain very effectively, <STRONG>however it comes at the expense of having the second lowest pvp damage output of any class. </strong>(Since we have no damage songs with a usable resist modifier, our melee is the only form of damage, which is second worst of all capable classes). I cannot cut through a wizard chain rune-ing, and thats assuming they are stationary.</div><DIV> </div><DIV>Am I saying wizards are misbalanced? Absolutely not. The best offensive capabilities with no utility. <STRONG>Tradeoffs, tradeoffs, tradeoffs</strong>. Every class is good at something, but can't do everything.</div><DIV> </div><DIV>Take manadrain if you like, in the POP era of pvp <STRONG>a safezone is 5 steps away at all times</strong>. No caster sits around oom waiting to die by my fury of papercuts. I know that if I actually want to fight somebody I can't even use manadrain or they'll run.</div><DIV> </div><DIV>That being said, I think its really good that people brought up safe zones. Taking those away, save for the bazaar, would be an incredible step in the right direction. I think we could consider this a huge success if the next patch weakened harmtouch and removed safezones.</div><br><hr></blockquote><br><br><br>Actually, I've been killed by bards quite a few times.  It usually ends up with them chaining 3 Tuvyen's on me for a base of 146/tick, not including any instruments or melee.  And while that may not seem like all that much it is quite literally impossible for me to do anything to the bard.  Which means that if I'm a significant distance from a zoneline then I will die.  And more than that where is the point to engaging in PvP with a bard?  In my opinion everyone should be at least somewhat vulnerable.  Even if it's only a little bit.  Right now bards simply aren't except to SKs, necros, and the occasional wizard.
