<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=PVP&message.id=161#M161">21</a> of 94
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 927 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<P><STRONG>"Now you have a whole group with the benefits of selos, best DS in the game, best resist buff in the game"</STRONG></P>
<P>Realisitically the only buff I can keep on anyone is selo because it lasts 2 minutes. The rest of the group bard songs in pvp look good on paper but lose their effectiveness in real applications. In other words the&nbsp;situation you list&nbsp;is hypothetical but not practical.&nbsp;I cannot stay within song range of my whole group, even part of it,&nbsp;at all times. Its not possible. If you think it is, play a bard then come back. In a 20 minute mass pvp battle my group&nbsp;will get less then 5 total pulses of any song other then selo.&nbsp;My group members rarely get a taste of anything but selo in pvp, and I am the most frequent pvping bard on the server.</P>
<P>Regarding the best DS in the game, usefull against rogues and other bards, thats it. Any other melee class uses a 2 hander and 90% of the time its a plankton. And once again its unfair to claim a bard could maintain the 2 songs it takes to generate that kind of DS on their entire group for the entire time. Once again, your gripes against bards are hypothetical but very impractical.</P>
<P><STRONG>"Actually, I've been killed by bards quite a few times. It usually ends up with them chaining 3 Tuvyen's on me for a base of 146/tick, not including any instruments or melee"</STRONG></P>
<P>You are speaking from experiences before the chant nerf. Additionally without an instrument its impossible to get 146 dmg/tick in <EM>pvp</EM>. I don't know where you are getting your numbers from.&nbsp; Now days for a bard to land a single chant it would take two resist checks (one for the DoT and one for the debuff) at a mere -50 modifier.&nbsp;A -50 modifier is a spit in the ocean.&nbsp;Everyone on a pvp server knows if it isn't unresistable, or at least a -200 check, it isn't even worth considering. So bard DoTs are no longer an arguable factor. They&nbsp;were nerfed to uselessness already sometime in February.</P>
<P><STRONG>"In my opinion everyone should be at least somewhat vulnerable."</STRONG></P>
<P>In order for said bard to hit you with ANY song he needs to be in spell range. Use faster casting spells, this has nothing to do with imbalance this has to do with you changing your tactics.&nbsp;If you want to argue invulnerability all I need to bring up is clerics. Their heals are so rediculously inexpensive and quick that they are neigh unkillable. A bard being difficult to kill is a tradeoff for being unable to kill anyone themselves.</P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P>Ultimately I think people need to stop attacking specific classes and address overall pvp problems like hillbugging, complete&nbsp;undispellability due to clickies, safezones, zone-healing, and near spell invulnerability due to rediculous resists on every item.</P>	
		</td></tr>
