			>
			<P>I still like the guild VS guild idea.. I think all the zeks are screwed right now with the exception of RZ which is hard to even call a PvP server.</P>
<P>My idea about the guild Vs guild PvP is the dynamic environment it creates for alliances. If one person wants to leave a guild or if a guild wants to leave an alliance they can do so without re-rolling as a lvl 1 character again just to switch teams. Teams wouldnt be imbalanced because you can have any class on any team. This is the nature of the beast. Sullon Zek is like 75% evil now and that is just LOL.</P>
<P>You might not be able to fix whats already broken but if you were able to make a new server and prevent it from failing in the first place, you wont have to ask 2 years from now "Where did we at soe go wrong?" Sullon Zek will never be fixed due to unfair team balancing and unfair territories, but this was explained on these very same boards during the beta. GM's and Dev's didn't want to listen back then but now they do? I wonder if that has anything to do with WoW, Vanguard, Dragon Empires, or Guildwars coming out. </P>
<P>Make a good hardcoded balanced team(guild-war) server without trains and the world will be a better place. No legends crap either. I would obviously quit EQ before playing on a blue server. Its like watching flies @#$#.</P>
