			<DIV>
<DIV>Alot of people derailed the PvP Dev thread thinking very MICRO, which isnt gonna help alot.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>The only Micro change they should make is to remove SK HT from PvP. </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Other than that, they should&nbsp;make macro changes to make PvP more fun by:</DIV>
<DIV>1. Stopping griefing -- </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><STRONG>Training</STRONG> had many good ideas on how to stop it -- </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><STRONG>Corpse camping </STRONG>make an NPC that can summon someone's corpse into a safe zone, but they lose some exp and cant be rezed if they do so.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><STRONG>Book/zoneline camping </STRONG>Make only the bazaar a safe zone, <EM>OR</EM> make it so that when someone zones into a safe zone from a PvP zone, that they are still attackable for 2-5 minutes, and if anyone attacks them, they also become attackable until their attackable status ends, or they avoid PvP (ie, no casting or melee)&nbsp;for 2-5 minutes.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>2.&nbsp; Add PvP content --&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV><STRONG>Rewards for PvP </STRONG>-- this is OK, it encourages PvPing, but it also encourages 5 on 1 gank squads running around too.&nbsp; Not bad, but not wonderful either.&nbsp; It will piss off alot of people to get ganked that way, which isnt great for PvP population.&nbsp; To counter this, they should . . . </DIV>
<DIV><STRONG>Mass PvP Zones - </STRONG>add zones that encourage mass PvP, siege zone scenarios, where winning guild&nbsp;gets access to a really nice loot zone for a week, and winner has to defend the next week to continue with access, and defending is very difficult (not impossible but very difficult).&nbsp; </DIV></DIV>	
